Cook noodles according to package direction; drain. Meanwhile, cook sausage in large skillet until no longer pink, stirring to break up sausage; drain. Add tomato sauce, undrained tomatoes and broth; bring to boil. Reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes. Combine ricotta cheese, egg and salt. Layer 1/3 noodles, 1/2 meat sauce, 1/3 noodles, all ricotta cheese mixture, 1/2 mozzarella cheese, remaining noodles, remaining meat sauce and remaining mozzarella cheese in 13x9 inch baking dish. Cover and bake in preheated 350 degrees F oven, 30 minutes. Bake, uncovered, 15 minutes or until bubbly.